,"meanings":["Pet form of   Emma  ,   Emily  , and related names, now used increasingly as an independent given name."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":83,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":92,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":103,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Emme Knight was born about 1466, in Laughton, Leicestershire, England, her father, John Knight, was 32 and her mother, Alianore Beauchamp, was 30. She had at least 1 son with William Foster. She died in Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1466–":"umbes 1466–Surnud","1460–Male":"1460–Surnud","1462–Female":"1462–Surnud","1464–Male":"1464–Surnud","1466–Female":"1466–Surnud","1468–1541":"1468–1541","1470–Female":"1470–Surnud","1472–Male":"1472–Surnud","1474–Female":"1474–Surnud","1465–1555":"1465–1555","1490–1555":"1490–1555","1435–1472":"1435–1472","1437–Female":"1437–Surnud","1462":"1462","1472":"1472","1460":"1460","1470":"1470","149